\fs28 Short exploration of principles of the economic simulation:\par

\pard\sl276\slmult1\fs32 -Population-\fs18\par
The population is the core principle behind demand and the companies behavior.\par
\fs32 -Economic Group-\fs18\par
The population wil find themselve as one of 5 types of consumer for each type of demands and products or services associated to concerned type of demands:\par
\tab\ul Subminimal Consumer : 0 to 5$ a day\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Minimal Consumer : 5 to 10$ a day\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Average Consumer : 10 to 20$ a day\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Above Average Consumer : 20 to 100$ a day\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Afluent Consumer : 100 to 200$ a day\par
\ulnone Each economic group is associated with 2 numbers. These numbers represent a range of daily spending capability.\par
-30 day rule-\par
This range is only representative of a daily consumer habit, it is however cumulative on a period of 30 day. Which means that\par
\tab\ul Subminimal Consumer are able to spend 150$ on a 30 day window,\ulnone\par
\tab\ul Minimal Consumer are able to spend 300$ on a 30 day window.\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Average Consumer are able to spend 600$ on a 30 day window.\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Above Average Consumer are able to spend 3000$ on a 30 day window.\par
\ulnone\tab\ul Afluent Consumer are able to spend 6000$ on a 30 day window.\ulnone\par
\line\fs32 -Needs-----------------------------------\fs18\par
Needs are the driving mecanism behind consumer and companies behavior.\par
\par
05-05-2025 NEEDS:\par
FOOD\par
ENTERTAINMENT\par
-----------------\par
Each need have different quota for each economic group.\par
For exemple subminimal consumer will indulge in entertainment either if it's free or if they can meet their more important need like food.\par
In principle each group has to meet the 30 day rule, which means, 30 units of premordial need as to be available to them before they will spend elsewhere or in more quantity.\par
However complexity arise in the fact that individual of a population has various liking and consumption habits.\par
For exemple in a pool of a 1000 people, 100 people despite their economic group will consider that 30 units of food is the bare minimum and if they can get more they will prioritize their spendings.\par
